title: For Sale:  1968 S&W Model 10
location: N. Col/Harris co., Columbus, GA, Georgia
postcontent: And here's another old favorite I'm letting go (sadly, I can't afford to keep 'em all, sometimes, something's gotta go!). This is the all-time classic  .38 duty revolver, the Model 10,  that's been in service with police and militaries, all over the world, for the entire last century, and still is today. This Model 10 is a VERY early D-series (ser# D8***), that according to S&W's serial number info, was manufactured in very early 1968 (or more likely, late '67). This pistol is about as nice as you're going to find (it actually looks considerably nicer in person than in these pics). It's very clean and low miles, minimal flame cutting, tight lock-up, and the blued finish is gorgeous, with only a small amount of the normal and unavoidable bluing wear on the usual edges. The case-coloring on the  trigger and hammer is immaculate. The factory original walnut magna grips are serial numbered to the gun. Not much else to say, the pistol is about as clean and solid as they get, externally and mechanically. And again, in a (probably) vain attempt to sidestep the scammers, I ask that you please try and sound like a legitimate local buyer, or I won't respond at all ( but also keep in mind that messages often just get lost here).  Buyer must be legal to own firearms, and be Ga resident over 21, with valid ID. As always, I'll show my Ga DL and carry permit. I'm ok with a bill-of-sale, or not. No checks, no shipping, no travel.  Price is $400 (hell, a friggin' Rossi or Taurus is gonna cost about that much ,LOL! These are typically in the $450-500 range, and not as vintage as this one.) No trade interests (unless it's something just crazy and irresistably in my favor! But, I might consider a clean, decent quality hardtail mountain bike.)Thanks for looking........M.
